    <body>
        <p>You can natively read your application secrets in <MadCap:variable name="General.Liquibase" /> with the <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="secrets.hashicorp"><a href="https://www.hashicorp.com/products/vault">Hashicorp Vault</a></MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="secrets.aws"><a href="https://aws.amazon.com/secrets-manager/">AWS Secrets Manager</a></MadCap:conditionalText> extension. If you connect to your vault using the <code class="language-text"><MadCap:variable name="General.liquiPropFile" /></code> file, you can store sensitive <MadCap:variable name="General.Liquibase" /> authentication details such as database <code class="language-text">url</code>, <code class="language-text">username</code>, and <code class="language-text">password</code>&#160;<MadCap:variable name="General.Param/Attribute" />s and your <MadCap:variable name="General.LBPro" /> license key in your vault.</p>
        <p>For more information, see <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="secrets.hashicorp"><a href="https://developer.hashicorp.com/vault">HashiCorp Vault documentation</a></MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="secrets.aws"><a href="https://docs.aws.amazon.com/secretsmanager/latest/userguide/intro.html">AWS Secrets Manager documentation</a></MadCap:conditionalText>.</p>
        <h2 id="requirements">Requirements</h2>
        <ul>
            <li><MadCap:variable name="General.Liquibase" />&#160;4.1<MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="secrets.aws,secrets.hashicorp">8</MadCap:conditionalText>.0+</li>
            <li><MadCap:variable name="General.LBPro" /> license. See <MadCap:xref href="../../../liquibase-pro/license-key.htm">How to Apply Your [%=General.LBPro%] License Key</MadCap:xref></li>
            <li MadCap:conditions="secrets.hashicorp"><a href="https://www.hashicorp.com/products/vault">HashiCorp Vault</a> 1.4.x+ with <a href="https://developer.hashicorp.com/vault/docs/secrets/kv/kv-v"><code>kv</code> secrets engine</a> v1 or v2 enabled</li>
            <li MadCap:conditions="secrets.aws"><a href="https://aws.amazon.com/secrets-manager/">AWS Secrets Manager</a> credentials</li>
            <li MadCap:conditions="secrets.aws">
                <MadCap:xref href="../../../liquibase-pro/aws/install-aws-extension.htm">Install the [%=General.LBPro%] AWS Extension</MadCap:xref>
            </li>
        </ul>
        <h2 id="installation" MadCap:conditions="secrets.hashicorp">Installation</h2>
        <h3 MadCap:conditions="secrets.hashicorp">CLI</h3>
        <ol MadCap:conditions="secrets.hashicorp">
            <li>Navigate to the <a href="https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.liquibase.ext.vaults/liquibase-hashicorp-vault">liquibase-hashicorp-vault</a> extension on Maven Central</li>
            <li>Download <code class="language-text">liquibase-<code>hashicorp-vault</code>-&lt;version&gt;.jar</code> and move it to the <code class="language-text">liquibase/lib</code> directory</li>
        </ol>
        <h3 MadCap:conditions="secrets.hashicorp">Maven</h3>
        <p MadCap:conditions="secrets.hashicorp">If you use Maven, add the <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="secrets.hashicorp"><a href="https://mvnrepository.com/artifact/org.liquibase.ext.vaults/liquibase-hashicorp-vault">HashiCorp Vault extension dependency</a></MadCap:conditionalText> in your <code class="language-text">pom.xml</code> file to download the JAR:</p><pre xml:space="preserve" MadCap:conditions="secrets.hashicorp"><code class="language-text">&lt;dependency&gt;
    &lt;groupId&gt;org.liquibase.ext.vaults&lt;/groupId&gt;
    &lt;artifactId&gt;liquibase-hashicorp-vault&lt;/artifactId&gt;
    &lt;version&gt;1.0.0&lt;/version&gt;
&lt;/dependency&gt;</code></pre>
        <h3 MadCap:conditions="secrets.hashicorp"><MadCap:variable name="General.Liquibase"></MadCap:variable> Package Manager</h3>
        <p MadCap:conditions="secrets.hashicorp">Alternatively, you can install the HashiCorp Vault extension with <code class="language-text">lpm</code> (<a href="https://github.com/liquibase/liquibase-package-manager">Liquibase Package Manager</a>).</p><pre xml:space="preserve" MadCap:conditions="secrets.hashicorp"><code class="language-shell">lpm update
lpm add liquibase-hashicorp-vault</code></pre>
        <h2 id="setup" MadCap:conditions="secrets.aws">Setup</h2>
        <p MadCap:conditions="secrets.aws"><a href="https://docs.aws.amazon.com/cli/latest/userguide/cli-configure-files.html">Configure your AWS credentials</a> in any standard method. <code class="language-text">aws_access_key_id</code>, <code class="language-text">aws_secret_access_key</code> and <code class="language-text">aws_region</code> are required.</p>
        <h2 id="usage">Usage</h2>
        <p>You can store any <MadCap:variable name="General.Liquibase" /> property in <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="secrets.hashicorp">HashiCorp Vault</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="secrets.aws">AWS Secrets Manager</MadCap:conditionalText>.</p>
        <ol>
            <li MadCap:conditions="secrets.hashicorp">Set the <code class="language-text">VAULT_ADDR</code> and <code class="language-text">VAULT_TOKEN</code>&#160;<MadCap:variable name="General.Param/Attribute" />s as <a href="../../../concepts/connections/liquibase-environment-variables.htm">environment variables</a>, as <a href="../../../concepts/connections/java-opts-environment-variable.htm"><code>-D</code> Java system properties</a>, or in your <a href="../../../concepts/connections/creating-config-properties.html"><code><MadCap:variable name="General.liquiPropFile" /></code> file</a>, OR as a command line attribute as shown in the command line section below.</li>
            <li>In <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="secrets.hashicorp">HashiCorp Vault</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="secrets.aws">AWS Secrets Manager</MadCap:conditionalText>, configure sensitive properties like your database username, password, URL, and <MadCap:variable name="General.LBPro" /> license key as secrets.</li>
            <li MadCap:conditions="secrets.hashicorp">Gather the <a href="https://developer.hashicorp.com/vault/api-docs">Vault HTTP API</a> path of each secret in your vault. For example, <code class="language-text">/v1/secret/data/test_secrets</code>.</li>
            <p class="note" MadCap:conditions="secrets.hashicorp" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;Note: &lt;/b&gt;">If you use <code class="language-text">kv</code> secrets engine v1, your HTTP API path will look like <code class="language-text">/v1/secret/example</code>. If you use <a href="https://developer.hashicorp.com/vault/docs/secrets/kv/kv-v2#acl-rules"><code>kv</code> secrets engine v2</a>, the path uses an additional "<code class="language-text">data</code>" prefix and will look like <code class="language-text">/v1/secret/data/example</code>. (The version number at the beginning of the API path is from the Vault HTTP API and is not related to the version of <code class="language-text">kv</code> you use.)</p>
            <li MadCap:conditions="secrets.aws">Gather the secret name  of each secret in your vault. For example, <code class="language-text">my-database-secret</code>.</li>
            <li>In your <code class="language-text"><MadCap:variable name="General.liquiPropFile" /></code> file or other valid configuration location, specify each of those <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="secrets.hashicorp">API paths</MadCap:conditionalText><MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="secrets.aws">names</MadCap:conditionalText> as the values of <MadCap:variable name="General.Liquibase" /> parameters, such as <code class="language-text">url</code>. <b MadCap:conditions="secrets.hashicorp">Omit the <code class="language-text">/v1/</code> at the beginning of the API path.</b> Use the syntax <code MadCap:conditions="secrets.hashicorp" class="language-text">VAULT,PATH,FIELD</code><code MadCap:conditions="secrets.aws" class="language-text">VAULT,SECRET,KEY</code>. <MadCap:conditionalText MadCap:conditions="secrets.aws">You can also enable support for AWS Systems Manager with <code class="language-text">VAULT,PARAMETER</code>.</MadCap:conditionalText></li>
            <p class="tip" MadCap:conditions="secrets.hashicorp" MadCap:autonum="&lt;b&gt;Tip: &lt;/b&gt;">If your <code class="language-text">PATH</code> includes whitespace, you must surround it with quotes. For example: <code class="language-text">"secret/my path/"</code>.</p>
        </ol>
